          "message": "fix: disable gradient tracking on all nn.Parameter for inference (#574)\n\n* fix: disable gradient tracking on all nn.Parameter for inference\n\nAdd `ATOM_REQUIRES_GRAD` env var (default: disabled) and a centralized\n`atom_parameter()` factory in `atom/model_ops/utils.py`.  Replace every\n`nn.Parameter(...)` constructor call across the codebase with\n`atom_parameter(...)` so gradient behaviour is controlled from a single\nplace.\n\nFixes flydsl/dlpack \"Can't export tensors that require gradient\" crash\nseen on GLM-5.1-MXFP4 CI (aiter >= 0.1.12) where `lm_head.weight`\npassed through `tgemm.mm → flydsl_hgemm → __dlpack__` with\n`requires_grad=True`.\n\nRoot cause: `nn.Parameter` defaults to `requires_grad=True`, and ATOM\n(an inference engine) never explicitly disabled it.\n\n* fix: guard requires_grad for non-differentiable dtypes\n\nOnly enable gradient tracking when the tensor is floating-point or\ncomplex. Integer/quantized dtypes (i8, i4x2, fp8_e8m0) do not support\ngradients in PyTorch and would raise at nn.Parameter construction time\nif ATOM_REQUIRES_GRAD=1.",
          "timestamp": "2026-04-15T22:32:04+08:00",
          "tree_id": "9ad0ecc1b7484254fc5e9ca5ab1bf2f84e3fd571",
          "url": "https://github.com/ROCm/ATOM/commit/179243d4056bdf6a488e15a83adc1cdb4fb68d88"
